    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-09-26T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-09-26T10:00:00-05:00" n="122"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d122">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.00/9–2645: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Greece</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacVeagh</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Athens</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-09-26T17:00:00+02:00"
                            >September 26, 1945—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received September 27—8:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1082. In reply urtel 59, Sept. 24.<note n="29" xml:id="d122fn29">Same as telegram
                        9875, September 24, 4 p.m., <ref target="#pg_161">p. 161</ref>.</note>
                    Matter being concerted with British, French colleagues in accordance your wishes
                    but Frenchman still awaiting instructions (mytel 103 Sept. 25).<note n="30"
                        xml:id="d122fn30">Same as telegram 1077, September 25, 7 p.m., <ref
                            target="#pg_161">p. 161</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Sent London as 105 repeated Dept as 1082.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacVeagh</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
